    "Lemma 5.19.",
    "Suppose ρ ∈ L ∞ ([0, 1] d) with ∥ρ∥ ∞ ≤ 2 and V is a weak * open neighbourhood of ρ.",
    "Then there exists some K 0 such that for every K ≥ K 0 and for every k ∈ N, the function refine[k] ρ ∈ V. Proof.",
    "Recall the definition of the initial rectangle R 0 = [0, 1 K] × [0, 1] d-1.",
    "We clearly have L d (R 0) → 0 as K → ∞."
  ]
}